						               													<description>Welcome to Pandorum&amp;mdash;a far-far away and unfriendly planet. No life, no breathable atmosphere, but lots of exploitable resources! For three long star cycles, the Galactic Council considered the issue of the planet&amp;rsquo;s colonization. Meanwhile, four largest space corporations managed to deploy their harvesters&amp;mdash;huge construction and production platforms&amp;mdash;on the Pandorum&amp;rsquo;s orbit.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Now when the decision has been made, at last, it&amp;rsquo;s time to start landing on the spotted with calderas planet&amp;rsquo;s surface! Take command over engineering services, construct production sites, update harvesters, build fortifications, elaborate logistics and infrastructure&amp;#10;for the planet. Don&amp;rsquo;t forget about your rivals: they are wide awake to rob you of your earned Quids&amp;mdash;intergalactic currency.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Everything you see in Pandorum is of utmost quality: simple rules with deep gameplay, high replayability, excellent components quality.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- The game idea belongs to the &amp;laquo;Trehgrannik&amp;raquo; group - the authors of &amp;ldquo;Game of Trains&amp;rdquo; and winners of UK Games Expo Best Card Game 2016 (UK Games Expo Best Card Game);&amp;#10; - The cover was designed by Alex Andreev, the well-known artist in the art community (the Roadside Picnic by Sony Pictures, images for Cirque du Soleil, Koo! Kin-Dza-Dza, etc.);&amp;#10; - The artwork was created by Pavel Maksimenko, a talented and seasoned art-director;&amp;#10; - Pandorum was officially presented, tested and well-received at Spiel&amp;rsquo;2017 in Germany.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
